1
00:00:53,360 --> 00:00:54,400
Let go!

2
00:00:56,240 --> 00:00:56,960
Qiuqiu!

3
00:00:57,840 --> 00:00:58,560
Qiuqiu.

4
00:00:59,240 --> 00:01:02,370
You are the Queen of the Lincang Drum Circle, aren't you?

5
00:01:03,240 --> 00:01:04,720
Look whose turf this is.

6
00:01:05,080 --> 00:01:06,960
You're here scamming people every day.

7
00:01:06,960 --> 00:01:07,890
I'm telling you,

8
00:01:07,920 --> 00:01:09,000
if you don't get lost,

9
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:09,800
I'm calling the cops.

10
00:01:09,800 --> 00:01:10,440
Don't run if you have guts!

11
00:01:10,440 --> 00:01:12,160
Don't think you're all that just because you're the Queen.

12
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:13,039
Just you wait!

13
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:19,080
Anan, are you a fool?

14
00:01:19,360 --> 00:01:21,420
How could you fall for such a scammer?

15
00:01:26,760 --> 00:01:27,360
Bro.

16
00:01:30,680 --> 00:01:31,400
It's over.

17
00:01:33,440 --> 00:01:34,240
Are you okay?

18
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:37,160
Let me see.

19
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:48,200
Two idiots.

20
00:01:51,360 --> 00:01:52,240
Cool.

21
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:53,770
Who is this girl?

22
00:01:55,360 --> 00:01:56,420
Is she your friend?

23
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:58,400
Don't talk nonsense.

24
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:00,360
She's not my girlfriend.

25
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:05,530
Who said anything about a girlfriend?

26
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:08,889
She plays the drums.

27
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:10,759
Qiuqiu is something else.

28
00:02:10,759 --> 00:02:12,690
She's the best drummer in Lincang.

29
00:02:12,880 --> 00:02:13,680
That's right.

30
00:02:13,880 --> 00:02:15,540
We can ask her about the drums.

31
00:02:25,920 --> 00:02:27,720
Not bad. You fight really well.

32
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:34,079
Are you serious?

33
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:36,480
You weren't scared fighting the scammers.

34
00:02:36,480 --> 00:02:37,540
But now you're shy?

35
00:02:39,640 --> 00:02:41,900
That's because he was bad-mouthing you.

36
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:50,850
How much longer are you going to stare?

37
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:53,640
What?

38
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:55,530
Trying to be my door god?

39
00:02:56,920 --> 00:02:57,520
Um...

40
00:02:57,720 --> 00:02:58,480
Qiuqiu,

41
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:00,040
I...

42
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:02,160
I just want to...

43
00:03:02,960 --> 00:03:03,800
We...

44
00:03:04,920 --> 00:03:06,680
He wants to start a band with you.

45
00:03:06,680 --> 00:03:07,360
No.

46
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:09,440
You can think about it first.

47
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:10,700
Then answer you? Sure.

48
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,160
Sure.

49
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:14,960
Looking for a drummer and not asking me?

50
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:16,490
That's not very cool of you.

51
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:17,280
What?

52
00:03:17,760 --> 00:03:18,880
Is my drumming

53
00:03:19,079 --> 00:03:20,320
not good enough for you?

54
00:03:20,320 --> 00:03:21,120
No, no, no.

55
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:24,240
It's because you're too good, so I...

56
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:25,120
Alright.

57
00:03:25,880 --> 00:03:28,010
But I have to listen to your song first.

58
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:30,329
I'll go borrow a guitar.

59
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:31,079
Wait.

60
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:32,900
I have a class soon.

61
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:42,600
By the way,

62
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:44,530
have you seen this drum?

63
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:46,280
I said I have to go to class.

64
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:47,730
Let's talk tonight.

65
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:48,800
Okay.

66
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:50,730
See you at my place tonight.

67
00:03:52,040 --> 00:03:52,900
Close the door.

68
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:55,920
What kind of door is this?

69
00:03:56,920 --> 00:03:57,520
Like this.

70
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:00,850
It's closed.

71
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:03,040
Get out.

72
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:15,620
I didn't expect this to be your style.

73
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:16,930
What did you say?

74
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:20,220
I told you to focus on riding. Don't get distracted.

75
00:04:26,440 --> 00:04:27,760
Did they give you a hard time?

76
00:04:27,760 --> 00:04:29,090
I'm fine. They let me go.

77
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:30,680
Alright.

78
00:04:30,960 --> 00:04:31,960
Since they let you go,

79
00:04:31,960 --> 00:04:33,820
find a chance to raise some money.

80
00:04:33,960 --> 00:04:35,560
If you really can't, just come back.

81
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:37,240
We'll figure something else out.

82
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:39,840
I'd thank God if you just stayed out of trouble.

83
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:41,000
I'm sorry, Liu Ma.

84
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:42,560
It's all my fault.

85
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:43,680
Be careful.

86
00:04:44,280 --> 00:04:44,940
Hanging up.

87
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:51,320
Why did you stop here?

88
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:52,840
I told you room and board are included.

89
00:04:52,840 --> 00:04:54,040
Hurry up and pack your things.

90
00:04:54,040 --> 00:04:56,300
We'll wait for Qiuqiu to get out of class.

91
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:57,080
Okay.

92
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:10,520
This is my home.

93
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:19,520
Are you a rich kid?

94
00:05:21,040 --> 00:05:22,920
This is the small B&B my parents run.

95
00:05:22,920 --> 00:05:24,600
So is the restaurant you went to that day.

96
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:25,120
No.

97
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:28,920
Don't tell me that village from the other day is yours too?

98
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:29,720
What village?

99
00:05:29,760 --> 00:05:30,880
That village.

100
00:05:31,280 --> 00:05:32,360
No, no.

101
00:05:33,040 --> 00:05:34,320
It's just a scenic spot.

102
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:35,480
They have ritual performances every day.

103
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:36,920
I just go help out with the show occasionally.

104
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:38,200
You two are so slow.

105
00:05:38,520 --> 00:05:40,000
Your mom will be back soon.

106
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:41,520
Coming.

107
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:44,840
My mom doesn't let me play music.

108
00:05:44,840 --> 00:05:47,100
I only practice when they're not around.

109
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:52,330
Go ahead.

110
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:53,159
What is it?

111
00:05:53,280 --> 00:05:53,880
This.

112
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:55,930
Have you seen this drum before?

113
00:06:00,840 --> 00:06:01,320
You.

114
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:02,520
Come here.

115
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,120
Bro, wait a second.

116
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:27,280
What's wrong?

117
00:06:28,840 --> 00:06:30,640
Isn't that the guy on the poster?

118
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:31,320
Yeah.

119
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:32,760
Liu Ma. My idol.

120
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:34,810
Why is he looking for a drum?

121
00:06:36,159 --> 00:06:37,240
He's helping me start a band.

122
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:38,280
I'm helping him find someone.

123
00:06:38,280 --> 00:06:38,960
Him?

124
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:42,880
That's why I say you're a fool.

125
00:06:43,080 --> 00:06:44,920
Someone like him starting a band with you?

126
00:06:44,920 --> 00:06:46,120
Use your head.

127
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:47,800
Don't get scammed again.

128
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:48,880
I believe him.

129
00:06:49,760 --> 00:06:50,620
Suit yourself.

130
00:06:52,159 --> 00:06:53,090
That wooden drum

131
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:55,040
was made by Sai Meng's father.

132
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:55,600
Right.

133
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:58,200
Right.

134
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:01,280
How could I forget Sai Meng's surname is also Yan?

135
00:07:01,280 --> 00:07:03,880
His family moved out of the village so long ago.

136
00:07:05,640 --> 00:07:07,160
After the insect plague in '99,

137
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:09,890
his family stayed on the tea mountain to grow tea.

138
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:11,440
Then it all adds up.

139
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:21,300
Look familiar?

140
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:22,490
I've seen your show.

141
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:25,080
I've dreamed of starting a band with you.

142
00:07:25,080 --> 00:07:26,540
Today, my dream came true.

143
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:27,680
This feeling...

144
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:29,810
it's like watching a feel-good drama.

145
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:32,000
I can't believe

146
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:32,960
this is real.

147
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:34,000
That drum.

148
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:36,980
By the way, Bro.

149
00:07:37,320 --> 00:07:38,440
Do you remember that day,

150
00:07:38,440 --> 00:07:40,400
the family we saw by the river?

151
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:41,620
I remember.

152
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:43,960
The person you're looking for is right there.

153
00:07:43,960 --> 00:07:45,090
It's too late today.

154
00:07:45,640 --> 00:07:47,770
I'll take you there tomorrow morning.

155
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:50,720
Okay.

156
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:54,200
Are we listening to music today?

157
00:07:54,520 --> 00:07:55,180
Yes, we are.

158
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:56,240
I forgot about that.

159
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:57,000
Come with me.
